| **Column Name**         | **Description**                                                                   |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **RowID**               | Sequential row number assigned to each record in the dataset.                     |
| **ID**                  | Unique identifier for each crime incident.                                        |
| **CaseNumber**          | Official case number assigned by the police department.                           |
| **Date**                | Date and time when the crime occurred.                                            |
| **Block**               | Approximate street block where the crime took place (e.g., "013XX S SAWYER AVE"). |
| **IUCR**                | Illinois Uniform Crime Reporting (IUCR) code used to classify the offense.        |
| **PrimaryType**         | Main category of the crime (e.g., Theft, Battery, Assault).                       |
| **Description**         | Detailed description of the specific crime.                                       |
| **LocationDescription** | Type of location where the crime occurred (e.g., Apartment, Street, School).      |
| **Arrest**              | Indicates whether an arrest was made (`1 = Yes`, `0 = No`).                       |
| **Domestic**            | Indicates whether the crime was domestic-related (`1 = Yes`, `0 = No`).           |
| **Beat**                | Police beat responsible for the location of the incident.                         |
| **District**            | Police district where the crime occurred.                                         |
| **Ward**                | Chicago city ward in which the incident occurred.                                 |
| **CommunityArea**       | Official Chicago community area code representing the neighborhood.               |
| **FBICode**             | FBI Uniform Crime Reporting (UCR) offense classification code.                    |
| **XCoordinate**         | Illinois State Plane X (East-West) coordinate used for mapping.                   |
| **YCoordinate**         | Illinois State Plane Y (North-South) coordinate used for mapping.                 |
| **Year**                | Year in which the crime occurred.                                                 |
| **UpdatedOn**           | Date and time when the crime record was last updated by the police department.    |
| **Latitude**            | Geographic latitude of the crime location.                                        |
| **Longitude**           | Geographic longitude of the crime location.                                       |
